&gt; in the-” the necromancer said. “Kill them! 
&gt; Do not let them take what is mine!” 
&gt; Gar and Fornak rushed forward to do battle. 
&gt; The Master began weaving his hands and 
&gt; speaking in the arcane tongue of 
&gt; magic-users. Crimson swung his arm down, 
&gt; grabbed a stone and in one fluid motion 
&gt; threw the stone at the leader elf. The rock 
&gt; caught the unarmored elf in the head and he 
&gt; collapsed backward, falling off his horse. 
&gt; Crimson grinned wryly and unsheathed his 
&gt; sword. 
&gt; “Uncle!” Elenya cried. Tears welled up in 
&gt; her eyes as her uncle collapsed to the 
&gt; ground and did not rise. She screamed again 
&gt; when hands grabbed her waist. Suddenly a 
&gt; hand covered her mouth and she heard a voice 
&gt; from behind speak softly. “We do not want to 
&gt; alert the humans.” 
&gt; The speaker lifted her off the horse and 
&gt; turned her around. Seeing his face, Elenya 
&gt; said, “Glodain! You’re alive!” 
&gt; “Yes, thanks to your uncle.” Glodain bent 
&gt; down and cut the ropes that bound her feet. 
&gt; He then cut the bonds on her wrists. 
&gt; Elenya stretched her hands and legs. “That 
&gt; feels much better. Quickly, let’s help my 
&gt; uncle’s men.” She turned to cast a spell 
&gt; when a strong hand grabbed her hand. Elenya 
&gt; turned to see Glodain holding her back. 
&gt; “What is it? I thought you wanted to kill 
&gt; that shadow knight.” 
&gt; “I would love to, but your uncle ordered me 
&gt; to bring you home. I must obey.” 
&gt; “What are you talking about? If you are not 
&gt; going to fight, let me go,” Elenya said, 
&gt; trying to squirm free from his grip. When 
&gt; she realized what he said, she stopped 
&gt; squirming. “Ordered?” 
&gt; “I will explain later, but now we must 
&gt; leave.” 
&gt; “Sorry to interrupt this reunion, but could 
&gt; someone please untie me?” 
&gt; Glodain turned toward the voice to see 
&gt; another body on the horse. He had been so 
&gt; centered on his mission he failed to realize 
&gt; the other person. “Who are you?” 
&gt; “I am Dauthi, graduate of the Bardic 
&gt; Collegium, full bard and singster.” 
&gt; Glodain snickered. He always knew that bards 
&gt; and halflings were the ones most likely to 
&gt; run into trouble with the law. Even if 
&gt; Crimson was far from a law-abiding citizen, 
&gt; this bard was still tied up. “I’ll have you 
&gt; free in a moment.” 
&gt; After his bonds were cut, Dauthi stretched 
&gt; his limbs and fingers. “Ah yes, that feels 
&gt; much better. Thank you… Glodain is it?” 
&gt; The wood elf nodded in response. “We will 
&gt; talk later, now we need to put as much 
&gt; distance from these people as possible. 
&gt; Elenya, you know the way.” 
&gt; Elenya nodded and cast one final glance at 
&gt; the battle. She then turned and ran into the 
&gt; brush, shortly followed by Dauthi. Glodain 
&gt; cast one final glance at the shadow knight. 
&gt; He considered disobeying his orders for a 
&gt; second and then shook his head. His family’s 
&gt; honor was more important than his vengeance. 
&gt; With a sigh, Glodain jumped into the brush 
&gt; behind Elenya and Dauthi. 
&gt; * * * 
&gt; Taurmon lifted himself off the ground and 
&gt; shook his head. “Ugh, my head,” he said. 
&gt; Looking around him, his heart dropped. All 
&gt; four of his knights were dead. Two were 
&gt; withered husks of their former selves and 
&gt; the other two had been slashed many times 
&gt; over. Two humans also lay on the ground. 
&gt; Taurmon grabbed his sword and rose to his 
&gt; feet, but was unable to stand for long. He 
&gt; collapsed to his knees and kneeled before 
&gt; the scene. The red-haired man walked over to 
&gt; him. His sword was coated in blood and 
&gt; Taurmon could see his own death in the man’s 
&gt; eyes. 
&gt; “Rodcet, deliver me!” Taurmon cried. 
&gt; Crimson smiled wickedly. “Wrong god, elf.” 
&gt; The shadow knight’s blade quickly descended 
&gt; and robbed the elf’s body of its head. 
&gt; Crimson stared at the headless corpse, still 
&gt; in its kneeling position, for a second and 
&gt; then kicked it over. His revelry was broken 
&gt; by the Master’s scream. 
&gt; “Crimson, you son of an orc, you let them 
&gt; escape!” 
</TEXTAREA></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE><TR>
